2 HOUSE BILL 1159
1 Article – Health – General
2 13–4701.
3 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
4 (c) “Program” means the Abortion Care Clinical Training Program.
5 13–4707.
6 On or before July 1 each year, the Department shall submit an annual report on the
7 Program to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article,
8 the General Assembly, THAT INCLUDES RECOMMENDATIONS ON ACTIONS THE STATE
9 CAN TAKE TO ENSURE THAT THERE ARE A SUFFICIENT NUMBER OF HEALTH
10 PROFESSIONALS TO PROVIDE ABORTION CARE IN THE STATE.
11 Article – Insurance
12 15–148.
13 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES WITH RESPECT TO:
14 (1) INSURERS AND NONPROFIT HEALTH SERVICE PLANS THAT
15 PROVIDE HOSPITAL, MEDICAL, OR SURGICAL BENEFITS TO INDIVIDUALS OR GROUPS
16 ON AN EXPENSE–INCURRED BASIS UNDER HEALTH INSURANCE POLICIES OR
17 CONTRACTS THAT ARE ISSUED OR DELIVERED IN THE STATE; AND
18 (2) HEALTH MAINTENANCE ORGANIZATIONS THAT PROVIDE
19 HOSPITAL, MEDICAL, OR SURGICAL BENEFITS TO INDIVIDUALS OR GROUPS UNDER
20 CONTRACTS THAT ARE ISSUED OR DELIVERED IN THE STATE.
21 (B) (1) EACH YEAR, THE COMMISSIONER SHALL COLLECT DATA FROM
22 THE ENTITIES SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION ON RECEIPTS, DISBURSEMENTS, ENDING
23 BALANCES, AND INTEREST FOR SEGREGATED ACCOUNTS ESTABLISHED UNDER §
24 1303(B)(2)(B) AND (C) OF THE FEDERAL PATIENT PROTECTION AND AFFORDABLE
25 CARE ACT AND 45 C.F.R. § 156.280.
26 (2) (I) ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1 EACH YEAR, THE
27 COMMISSIONER SHALL REPORT TO THE SENATE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THE
28 HOUSE HEALTH COMMITTEE, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE
29 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, ON THE AGGREGATE DATA COLLECTED UNDER
30 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.

HOUSE BILL 1159 3
1 (II) THE REPORT REQUIRED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF
2 THIS PARAGRAPH SHALL USE DATA COLLECTED FOR THE CALENDAR YEAR THAT IS
3 2 YEARS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING JANUARY 1 OF THE YEAR IN WHICH THE REPORT
4 IS DUE.
5 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
6 1, 2026.

